WEBVTT

00:01.372 --> 00:02.373
PREVIOUSLY ON "REVENGE"...

00:02.373 --> 00:03.374
DADDY!

00:03.374 --> 00:05.136
(Emily) WHEN I WAS A CHILD,

00:05.136 --> 00:06.177
MY FATHER WAS FRAMED FOR
A CRIME HE DIDN'T COMMIT.

00:06.177 --> 00:07.007
DADDY!

00:07.007 --> 00:08.509
AMANDA!
 YOU CAN'T STAY.

00:08.509 --> 00:10.511
I DON'T REMEMBER ASKING YOU
FOR YOUR PERMISSION.

00:10.511 --> 00:14.085
HOW MUCH WILL IT COST TO GET YOU
TO STOP SEEING MY DAUGHTER?

00:15.015 --> 00:16.047
OH, MY GOD.

00:16.047 --> 00:17.118
AMANDA?

00:17.118 --> 00:18.419
I WANT TO COME HOME, JACK.

00:20.191 --> 00:22.093
(Nolan) Tyler got hold
of a shredded speech

00:22.093 --> 00:24.095
exposing Conrad and Victoria.

00:24.095 --> 00:26.457
THIS IS SATOSHI TAKEDA.

00:26.457 --> 00:27.698
I FEAR I'M LOSING CONTROL.

00:27.698 --> 00:30.661
REVENGE IS A STONY PATH.

00:30.661 --> 00:33.664
(grunting)

00:37.368 --> 00:38.409
(grunts)

00:38.409 --> 00:39.470
AH.

00:39.470 --> 00:40.571
(grunts)

00:40.571 --> 00:42.813
YOU REMEMBER WELL.

00:42.813 --> 00:46.177
ONE THING YOU CAN COUNT ON,
I NEVER FORGET.

00:46.177 --> 00:48.179
(pants)

00:51.122 --> 00:52.123
(grunts)

00:53.424 --> 00:54.585
(chuckles)

00:54.585 --> 00:55.756
(grunts)

00:55.756 --> 00:57.188
(grunts)

00:57.188 --> 00:59.360
HOW DOES IT FEEL
NOW THAT YOUR TARGETS

00:59.360 --> 01:03.164
ARE NO LONGER MEER IDEAS,
BUT FLESH AND BONE?

01:03.164 --> 01:04.194
(pants)

01:05.596 --> 01:09.170
(speaking Japanese)

01:09.170 --> 01:10.841
(sighs and speaks indistinctly)

01:10.841 --> 01:12.143
(gasps)

01:12.143 --> 01:13.804
(grunts)

01:13.804 --> 01:15.346
THE TASK IN FRONT OF YOU

01:15.346 --> 01:17.678
REQUIRES ABSOLUTE FOCUS.

01:17.678 --> 01:19.510
(grunts)

01:20.611 --> 01:22.513
(grunts and pants)

01:22.513 --> 01:24.655
IF YOU LET YOUR EMOTIONS
GUIDE YOU,

01:24.655 --> 01:27.158
YOU WILL FAIL.

01:27.158 --> 01:29.760
(speaks Japanese)

01:29.760 --> 01:31.262
(speaks Japanese)

01:33.224 --> 01:36.697
PRIORITIZE THE OBSTACLES
TO YOUR END GOAL.

01:36.697 --> 01:38.229
ELIMINATE THEM...

01:38.229 --> 01:40.231
ONE AT A TIME.

01:42.333 --> 01:43.834
(both grunt)

01:43.834 --> 01:45.306
(pants)

01:45.306 --> 01:46.877
THERE ARE TWO OF THEM.

01:46.877 --> 01:48.108
(pants)

01:48.108 --> 01:51.382
TYLER. HE'S SIMPLE,
OR OUGHTA BE.

01:51.382 --> 01:53.214
AND THEN THERE'S AMANDA.

01:53.214 --> 01:56.447
(sighs)
SHE'S A TICKING TIME BOMB.

01:56.447 --> 01:58.889
THEN YOU MUST STAY CLEAR
OF THE BLAST.

01:58.889 --> 02:00.191
HOW?

02:00.191 --> 02:01.792
(grunts)

02:01.792 --> 02:03.594
(both grunting)

02:03.594 --> 02:07.127
ENGAGE YOUR ULTIMATE OPPONENT
TO DO THE WORK FOR YOU.

02:07.127 --> 02:08.199
UGH!

02:08.199 --> 02:11.562
(pants)

02:11.562 --> 02:13.204
VICTORIA?

02:13.204 --> 02:15.166
(pants)

02:20.441 --> 02:22.173
VICTORIA,

02:22.173 --> 02:23.574
GOOD MORNING.

02:23.574 --> 02:25.376
I MADE A BREAKFAST RESERVATION
FOR US

02:25.376 --> 02:26.817
SO WE COULD CONTINUE
OUR DISCUSSION

02:26.817 --> 02:28.148
FROM THE OTHER NIGHT.

02:28.148 --> 02:29.480
TODAY IS NOT A GOOD DAY,

02:29.480 --> 02:33.424
AND PLEASE CONTINUE
ADDRESSING ME ASMS.GRAYSON.

02:33.424 --> 02:36.187
OKAY, MY APOLOGIES.

02:36.187 --> 02:37.428
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

02:37.428 --> 02:40.561
CONRAD FILED FOR DIVORCE.

02:40.561 --> 02:42.162
I'VE HAD BETTER MORNINGS.

02:42.162 --> 02:44.795
WELL, DON'T WORRY. I'M SURE
YOU'LL COME OUT ON TOP.

02:44.795 --> 02:46.397
WHAT MAKES YOU SO SURE?

02:46.397 --> 02:48.299
WELL,
YOU'RE VICTORIA GRAYSON.

02:48.299 --> 02:49.800
YOU HAVE TWO CHILDREN
WHO LOVE YOU,

02:49.800 --> 02:51.502
FRIENDS WHO WOULD
DO ANYTHING FOR YOU,

02:51.502 --> 02:54.775
AN ENTIRE COMMUNITY
THAT WORSHIPS YOU.

02:54.775 --> 02:56.407
AND YOU HAVE ME.

02:56.407 --> 02:57.808
ANYTHING YOU NEED,

02:57.808 --> 02:59.250
I CAN TAKE CARE OF IT.

02:59.250 --> 03:01.712
CAN YOU BRING MY SON HOME
TO ME?

03:01.712 --> 03:05.256
I CAN CERTAINLY TRY.

03:05.256 --> 03:06.817
THANK YOU.

03:07.958 --> 03:10.190
ASHLEY.

03:10.190 --> 03:11.492
VICTORIA'S FINE.

03:15.696 --> 03:17.968
(sighs)

03:17.968 --> 03:19.470
(knock on door)

03:19.470 --> 03:20.571
(doorknob rattles)

03:20.571 --> 03:22.233
(Ashley) TYLER,
ARE YOU DECENT?

03:22.233 --> 03:24.375
OR MORE IMPORTANTLY,
ALONE?

03:24.375 --> 03:26.237
YEAH, COME ON IN.
(sighs)

03:26.237 --> 03:27.408
I WASN'T SURE I'D SEE YOU

03:27.408 --> 03:29.240
AFTER YOUR FREAK-OUT
AT THE INVESTMENT PARTY.

03:29.240 --> 03:31.442
FREAK-OUT?
I LET YOU OFF EASY.

03:31.442 --> 03:32.783
ONE MINUTE
I'M UNDER THE IMPRESSION

03:32.783 --> 03:34.415
WE MIGHT ACTUALLY HAVE
A FUTURE TOGETHER,

03:34.415 --> 03:37.548
AND THE NEXT I CATCH YOU
LIP-LOCKED WITH NOLAN ROSS.

03:37.548 --> 03:41.592
YEAH, WELL, AS UNPLEASANT
AS THAT WAS FOR YOU AND ME,

03:41.592 --> 03:44.295
THE EXTRA BIT OF ATTENTION
I PAID NOLAN

03:44.295 --> 03:45.956
WAS DONE WITH OUR FUTURE
IN MIND.

03:45.956 --> 03:48.729
NOLAN'S $20 MIL
IS BEING WIRED AS WE SPEAK.

03:48.729 --> 03:50.931
AND I'M HEADED IN
TO COLLECT MY COMMISSION.

03:50.931 --> 03:53.264
200 LARGE.

03:53.264 --> 03:56.467
YOU KISS A BILLIONAIRE ONCE,
YOU MAKE 200 GRAND.

03:56.467 --> 03:58.339
I HAVE BEEN KISSING
VICTORIA'S ASS ALL SUMMER,

03:58.339 --> 04:00.841
AND I'M LUCKY IF SHE LETS ME
CALL HER BY HER FIRST NAME.

04:00.841 --> 04:02.543
(chuckles)

04:02.543 --> 04:04.275
SO LET ME SHARE THE WEALTH.

04:04.275 --> 04:07.418
I HAVE A 9:00 RESERVATION
AT DRIFTWOOD TOMORROW NIGHT.

04:07.418 --> 04:09.420
I DON'T NEED TO TELL YOU
WHAT A HARD GET THAT IS.

04:09.420 --> 04:11.352
SO YOU'RE NOT EVEN BI?

04:11.352 --> 04:12.483
MM.

04:12.483 --> 04:13.984
WHAT I AM IS AMBITIOUS.

04:13.984 --> 04:17.488
IF YOU CAN'T HANDLE THAT,
THEN WE PART AS FRIENDS.

04:17.488 --> 04:20.361
BUT IF I WERE YOU, I'D
STRONGLY CONSIDER JOINING ME.

04:20.361 --> 04:21.661
NOW THAT I HAVE
A FOOTHOLD WITH GRAYSON,

04:21.661 --> 04:23.664
I'M CLIMBING ALL THE WAY
TO THE TOP.

04:23.664 --> 04:25.536
AND THIS INVITATION...
(chuckles)

04:25.536 --> 04:27.368
IT WON'T BE OPEN FOREVER.

04:27.368 --> 04:29.039
(chuckles)

04:30.471 --> 04:31.542
(door closes)

04:31.542 --> 04:32.973
(Amanda) JACK?

04:32.973 --> 04:34.975
YOU IN HERE?

04:34.975 --> 04:36.307
(barking)
 WHOA.

04:36.307 --> 04:38.048
CHILL, CUJO.

04:38.048 --> 04:40.050
(continues barking)
 (Jack) SAMMY.

04:40.050 --> 04:42.983
STOP. STOP IT. COME HERE.
 (whines)

04:42.983 --> 04:45.386
SORRY. HE'S GOT ISSUES
WITH STRANGERS.

04:45.386 --> 04:47.287
APPARENTLY, HE DOESN'T
REMEMBER THAT YOU AREN'T ONE.

04:47.287 --> 04:48.589
WELL, IT'S BEEN A WHILE.

04:48.589 --> 04:50.290
WELL, YEAH, AND HE'S

04:50.290 --> 04:52.292
MORE THAN A LITTLE SENILE.

04:52.292 --> 04:55.396
I WAS JUST BRINGING BREAKFAST
DOWN TO THE BOAT.

04:55.396 --> 04:56.997
YOU STILL LIKE
BLUEBERRY PANCAKES?

04:56.997 --> 05:00.371
(chuckles)
WHO DOESN'T LIKE PANCAKES?

05:04.475 --> 05:07.338
(sighs) I STILL REMEMBER
THE DAY I MET SAMMY.

05:07.338 --> 05:08.679
SAME DAY I MET YOU.

05:08.679 --> 05:10.441
(sighs)

05:10.441 --> 05:11.812
(laughs) ON THE BEACH...

05:11.812 --> 05:13.514
DOWN IN FRONT OF YOUR HOUSE.

05:13.514 --> 05:15.346
WE PLAYED TUG-OF-WAR WITH HIM
AND PIECE OF DRIFTWOOD.

05:15.346 --> 05:16.647
SORRY, UM...

05:16.647 --> 05:20.020
MEMORY LANE ISN'T EXACTLY
A ROAD I LIKE TO GO DOWN.

05:20.020 --> 05:22.092
NO, NO, NO.
OF COURSE. OF COURSE.

05:22.092 --> 05:23.454
I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND.

05:23.454 --> 05:25.626
I, UH, SWIPED
ONE OF YOUR SHIRTS.

05:25.626 --> 05:27.458
LOOKS BETTER ON YOU
THAN ME.

05:27.458 --> 05:28.659
(laughs)

05:28.659 --> 05:30.761
SO DID YOU MAKE A DECISION
ABOUT STICKING AROUND?

05:30.761 --> 05:33.464
(clicks tongue) YEAH.

05:33.464 --> 05:35.335
BUT IF I'M GONNA STAY
IN THE HAMPTONS,

05:35.335 --> 05:37.037
I'M GONNA NEED
SOME NEW CLOTHES.

05:37.037 --> 05:38.539
WANT TO PICK SOME OUT
WITH ME?

05:38.539 --> 05:40.511
I'D LOVE TO,
BUT I HAVEN'T FIGURED OUT

05:40.511 --> 05:42.042
HOW TO GET THE BAR
TO OPEN ITSELF.

05:42.042 --> 05:43.343
MM.

05:43.343 --> 05:44.875
(chuckles)

05:44.875 --> 05:48.419
I CAN'T TELL YOU HOW GOOD
IT FEELS TO HAVE YOU BACK.

05:50.521 --> 05:52.352
AND I CAN'T TELL YOU...

05:52.352 --> 05:55.586
HOW LONG IT'S BEEN SINCE
SOMEONE WAS THIS NICE TO ME.

05:56.827 --> 05:58.459
THANKS, JACK.

05:58.459 --> 06:00.831
YOU MAKE IT EASY.

06:02.893 --> 06:05.896
(Nolan)SOA QUICK RECAP

06:05.896 --> 06:07.738
IN CASE YOU'VE BEEN TOO BUSY
KNOCKING BOOTS

06:07.738 --> 06:09.540
WITH THE YOUNG GRAYSON
TO REMEMBER WHAT HAPPENED

06:09.540 --> 06:11.802
ON LAST WEEK'S EPISODE
OF "THE TYLER CHRONICLES."

06:11.802 --> 06:14.475
I REMEMBER, NOLAN.
GET TO THE POINT.

06:14.475 --> 06:15.776
WELL, AFTER TYLER
FINISHED APOLOGIZING

06:15.776 --> 06:19.780
FOR TAKING MY CREDIT CARD
ON A PETTY THEFT CRIME SPREE,

06:19.780 --> 06:23.414
HE STARTED GOOGLE STALKING
ONE DAVID CLARKE.

06:23.414 --> 06:24.955
TAKE A LOOK.
 (clicks keyboard key)

06:24.955 --> 06:27.117
(whooshes)

06:27.117 --> 06:28.519
(whale cam clicks,
computer whooshes)

06:28.519 --> 06:30.791
NOW CHECK OUT
MY BROWSER HISTORY.

06:30.791 --> 06:32.392
(clicks keyboard keys,
computer chirps)

06:32.392 --> 06:34.595
HAVE YOU WIRED MONEY
OVER TO GRAYSON GLOBAL YET?

06:34.595 --> 06:36.567
HAPPENING AS WE SPEAK.

06:36.567 --> 06:40.400
$20 MILLION.

06:40.400 --> 06:41.572
PULL IT BACK.

06:41.572 --> 06:43.103
MM. I DON'T THINK
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.

06:43.103 --> 06:44.935
(chuckles) WHAT?

06:44.935 --> 06:46.437
IF I PULL MY MONEY

06:46.437 --> 06:49.540
AND CRUSH TYLER'S CHANCES
OF BECOMING A GRAYSON, EMS,

06:49.540 --> 06:50.511
WHO KNOWS
WHAT HE'LL DO NEXT?

06:50.511 --> 06:51.682
WELL, HOPEFULLY,

06:51.682 --> 06:53.183
HE'LL TRY TO BLACKMAIL CONRAD

06:53.183 --> 06:54.885
WITH WHAT'S IN THAT SPEECH.

06:54.885 --> 06:56.817
OH, REALLY?

06:56.817 --> 06:58.188
I DON'T KNOW.

06:58.188 --> 07:01.191
I THOUGHT YOU HAD BIGGER,
BADDER PLANS FOR THE GRAYSONS.

07:01.191 --> 07:02.523
I DO.

07:02.523 --> 07:04.825
LYDIA'S SPEECH CONTAINS
INFORMATION NOT EVIDENCE.

07:04.825 --> 07:06.126
AND LET'S NOT FORGET,

07:06.126 --> 07:08.759
TYLER NO LONGER HAS IT
IN HIS POSSESSION, WE DO.

07:08.759 --> 07:11.431
WHICH YOU NEVER
THANKED ME FOR, BY THE WAY.

07:11.431 --> 07:13.003
I'LL THANK YOU WHEN TYLER'S
OUT OF THE PICTURE.

07:13.003 --> 07:14.605
OH.

07:14.605 --> 07:15.706
UNLESS, OF COURSE,

07:15.706 --> 07:19.009
YOU HAVE YOUR OWN REASONS
FOR KEEPING HIM AROUND.

07:19.009 --> 07:20.440
(chuckles)

07:20.440 --> 07:24.545
I'LL CALL MY BUSINESS MANAGER
THIS AFTERNOON.

07:24.545 --> 07:26.446
HOW ABOUT...

07:26.446 --> 07:28.849
YOU CALL HIM NOW?

07:31.722 --> 07:33.784
(cell phone clicks and beeps)

07:35.726 --> 07:38.529
NOLAN ROSS FOR BARRY JOSSLIN.

07:41.061 --> 07:44.935
(Nolan) YEAH, IT'S ABOUT MONEY.
WHY ELSE WOULD I CALL?

07:44.935 --> 07:46.637
(clicks)

07:46.637 --> 07:48.468
(clicks keyboard key)

07:49.640 --> 07:51.471
(click)

07:51.471 --> 07:53.544
(whooshes)

07:58.949 --> 08:01.211
(chuckles)

08:04.985 --> 08:06.156
(clicks)

08:06.156 --> 08:07.518
(click)

08:07.518 --> 08:08.488
(whoosh)

08:14.064 --> 08:17.067
♪♪♪

08:23.874 --> 08:25.075
(Daniel) MY FATHER
FILED FOR DIVORCE?

08:25.075 --> 08:26.206
WHY WOULDN'T HE
HAVE TOLD ME THIS MORNING?

08:26.206 --> 08:27.638
WHO KNOWS?

08:27.638 --> 08:30.210
BUT YOUR POOR MOTHER
IS BESIDE HERSELF.

08:30.210 --> 08:31.942
SHE REALLY NEEDS YOU
RIGHT NOW, DANIEL.

08:31.942 --> 08:33.283
IN FACT, SHE WAS HOPING
YOU'D JOIN HER FOR LUNCH.

08:33.283 --> 08:35.115
HEY.

08:35.115 --> 08:36.986
PERFECT TIMING.
 (mouths word)

08:36.986 --> 08:38.919
PLEASE JOIN ME FOR LUNCH
TODAY WITH MY MOTHER.

08:38.919 --> 08:41.221
YEAH, OF COURSE.
JUST TELL ME WHEN AND WHERE.

08:41.221 --> 08:44.224
1:00, DUMAS' ON MAIN.

08:44.224 --> 08:46.827
I'LL MODIFY THE RESERVATION
FOR THREE.

08:46.827 --> 08:47.998
BYE.

08:47.998 --> 08:51.131
THANKS, ASH.

08:51.131 --> 08:53.063
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

08:53.063 --> 08:56.236
IT SOUNDS LIKE MY PARENTS
ARE FINALLY GETTING A DIVORCE.

08:56.236 --> 09:00.270
OH, MY GOD.
I'M SO SORRY, DANIEL.

09:00.270 --> 09:01.872
THEY SEEMED...

09:01.872 --> 09:04.544
SO PERFECT TOGETHER.

09:04.544 --> 09:08.749
YEAH,
MAYBE A LONG TIME AGO.

09:08.749 --> 09:10.621
WELL,
MAYBE THEY'LL WORK IT OUT.

09:10.621 --> 09:12.222
I MEAN, WHO KNOWS?
IT MIGHT EVEN

09:12.222 --> 09:13.924
STRENGTHEN YOUR RELATIONSHIP
WITH BOTH OF THEM.

09:13.924 --> 09:16.556
YEAH, WITH MY MOM,
PERHAPS.

09:16.556 --> 09:18.759
YOU KNOW, I THINK MY DAD WOULD
RATHER HAVE TYLER FOR A SON

09:18.759 --> 09:20.230
THAN ME.

09:20.230 --> 09:22.562
WELL, IT'S HARD TO ARGUE
CONSIDERING THAT MY DAD'S

09:22.562 --> 09:24.595
BEEN TRYING TO LAND NOLAN
AS A CLIENT

09:24.595 --> 09:26.336
EVER SINCE
NOLCORP WENT PUBLIC.

09:26.336 --> 09:29.569
I GUESS TY HAS JUST GOT
THAT MAGIC TOUCH.

09:29.569 --> 09:31.101
I'LL SAY.

09:31.101 --> 09:32.673
WHAT'S THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

09:34.044 --> 09:37.007
THE ONLY REASON THAT NOLAN
INVESTED WITH YOUR FATHER

09:37.007 --> 09:40.110
IS BECAUSE
TYLER'S BLACKMAILING HIM.

09:40.110 --> 09:42.953
WAIT. BLACKMAILING HIM
WITH WHAT?

09:44.955 --> 09:46.116
OH.

09:46.116 --> 09:48.619
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
HOW MUCH E. COLI

09:48.619 --> 09:50.661
YOU JUST DUMPED
NEXT TO MY LUNCH?

09:50.661 --> 09:52.362
THERE'S A REASON
I DON'T CARRY CASH.

09:52.362 --> 09:53.894
AND THAT'S WHY.

09:53.894 --> 09:55.595
LIGHTEN UP, EEYORE.

09:55.595 --> 09:57.067
I'M PAYING YOU BACK
FOR ALL THE STUFF I BOUGHT

09:57.067 --> 09:59.229
ON YOUR CREDIT CARD,
LIKE I PROMISED.

09:59.229 --> 10:01.702
YOU DO YOU REALIZE
YOU'RE PAYING ME BACK

10:01.702 --> 10:03.974
WITH MY OWN MONEY,
RIGHT?

10:03.974 --> 10:05.836
I'M TRYING TO SAY THANK YOU.

10:05.836 --> 10:09.680
YOU HAVE NO IDEA THE DOORS
YOU OPENED UP FOR ME.

10:09.680 --> 10:11.942
WE SHOULD CELEBRATE,
GET OUT OF TOWN FOR THE WEEKEND,

10:11.942 --> 10:13.814
ON ME.

10:13.814 --> 10:16.216
YOU LIKE SOUTH BEACH?

10:16.216 --> 10:18.148
MIAMI'S FOR TROLLS.

10:18.148 --> 10:20.651
(laughs) OKAY, THEN.
YOU PICK THE PLACE.

10:20.651 --> 10:22.152
I JUST WANT TO SPEND SOME...

10:22.152 --> 10:24.094
QUALITY TIME WITH YOU.

10:24.094 --> 10:25.395
MM.

10:25.395 --> 10:27.928
(clicks tongue)

10:29.329 --> 10:33.333
MONTE CARLO'S PRETTY NICE
THIS TIME OF YEAR.

10:37.267 --> 10:39.009
(man) EXCUSE ME. VICTORIA.

10:39.009 --> 10:40.340
YES.

10:40.340 --> 10:41.842
I'M RYAN HUNTLEY.

10:41.842 --> 10:44.274
MICHAEL DAVIS INTRODUCED US
A COUPLE OF YEARS AGO

10:44.274 --> 10:45.976
AT AN ART AUCTION
AT SOTHEBY'S.

10:45.976 --> 10:48.819
YOU OUTBID ME
ON A SPECTACULAR KANDINSKY.

10:48.819 --> 10:51.682
I REMEMBER.
YOU COST ME A FORTUNE.

10:52.953 --> 10:54.354
FORGIVE ME
FOR BEING INDELICATE,

10:54.354 --> 10:56.226
BUT YOUR HUSBAND
ASKED TO RETAIN ME

10:56.226 --> 10:58.228
AS HIS DIVORCE ATTORNEY.

10:58.228 --> 11:01.762
AND YOU JUST HAPPENED
TO RUN INTO ME HERE?

11:01.762 --> 11:04.034
FOR REASONS OF MY OWN,
I DECLINED HIS OFFER.

11:04.034 --> 11:06.036
BUT BELIEVE ME WHEN I SAY,
I-I'D LOVE NOTHING MORE

11:06.036 --> 11:09.700
THAN TO REPRESENT YOU
AGAINST YOUR HUSBAND.

11:09.700 --> 11:12.672
(indistinct conversations)

11:12.672 --> 11:14.074
I'LL GIVE IT SOME THOUGHT.

11:14.074 --> 11:15.706
PLEASE DO.

11:15.706 --> 11:18.749
(Daniel) HEY, MOM.

11:18.749 --> 11:21.011
DANIEL, I'M SO GLAD
YOU COULD COME.

11:21.011 --> 11:22.352
OH.

11:22.352 --> 11:24.284
AND I SEE
THAT YOU BROUGHT EMILY.

11:24.284 --> 11:26.717
VICTORIA,
I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND.

11:26.717 --> 11:28.088
DANIEL TOLD ME EVERYTHING,

11:28.088 --> 11:31.792
AND WE JUST REALLY WANTED
TO COME AND SHOW OUR SUPPORT.

11:31.792 --> 11:33.724
I'M SURE
YOU MUST BE DEVASTATED.

11:33.724 --> 11:36.466
DEVASTATED IS NOT
THE WORD I WOULD USE.

11:36.466 --> 11:38.428
AND QUITE FRANKLY,

11:38.428 --> 11:41.301
MY MARRIAGE IS THE LAST THING
I WANT TO TALK ABOUT RIGHT NOW.

11:41.301 --> 11:43.303
WELL, WHY DON'T WE
TALK ABOUT TYLER?

11:43.303 --> 11:45.906
DON'T YOU THINK IT'S WEIRD HE'S
STILL LIVING IN THE POOL HOUSE

11:45.906 --> 11:47.237
EVEN THOUGH I'M STAYING
AT EMILY'S?

11:47.237 --> 11:48.779
QUITE THE OPPOSITE.

11:48.779 --> 11:51.211
WITH YOU GONE, I RATHER LIKE
HAVING HIM THERE.

11:51.211 --> 11:53.884
TYLER SEEMS
ALMOST LIKE FAMILY TO ME.

11:53.884 --> 11:55.786
OKAY, BUT HE'S NOT
AND HE NEVER WILL BE.

11:55.786 --> 11:58.718
I'D RATHER HAVE SOMEONE
IN THE HOUSE THAN NO ONE AT ALL.

11:59.950 --> 12:01.391
UNLESS OF COURSE
YOU'RE TELLING ME

12:01.391 --> 12:04.124
THAT YOU'RE PLANNING
ON MOVING BACK HOME.

12:04.124 --> 12:06.496
UH, NO. (sighs)

12:08.398 --> 12:10.500
MM. WELL, THEN...

12:10.500 --> 12:12.502
AS FAR AS I'M CONCERNED,
HE STAYS.

12:12.502 --> 12:15.365
(laughs)

12:15.365 --> 12:18.368
(indistinct conversations
continue)

12:20.410 --> 12:22.873
♪♪♪

12:22.873 --> 12:24.344
(indistinct conversations)

12:24.344 --> 12:26.346
HOW'S THE WONDER DOG?

12:26.346 --> 12:28.178
STARTING TO LOSE IT
A LITTLE, I'M AFRAID.

12:28.178 --> 12:29.780
HOW SO?

12:29.780 --> 12:31.051
I DON'T KNOW IF I TOLD YOU,

12:31.051 --> 12:32.452
AMANDA WAS HIS FIRST OWNER.

12:32.452 --> 12:34.124
BUT EVERY TIME HE SEES HER,
HE GOES CRAZY,

12:34.124 --> 12:35.385
AND NOT IN A GOOD WAY.

12:35.385 --> 12:36.827
WELL, THAT'S UNCOMFORTABLE.

12:36.827 --> 12:38.258
YEAH, WELL, TO BE FAIR,

12:38.258 --> 12:39.790
I DON'T THINK SHE REMEMBERS
MUCH ABOUT HIM EITHER.

12:39.790 --> 12:41.491
SHE'S BLOCKED OUT
MOST OF HER CHILDHOOD.

12:41.491 --> 12:43.263
AND SHE REALLY HATES
TALKING ABOUT IT.

12:43.263 --> 12:44.464
HMM. IS SHE AROUND?

12:44.464 --> 12:46.236
CLOTHES SHOPPING.

12:46.236 --> 12:49.369
SHE DECIDED TO STICK AROUND
AND FACE HER DEMONS.
 (whines)

12:49.369 --> 12:51.501
YEAH, SHE SEEMS TO HAVE
A LOT OF THOSE.

12:51.501 --> 12:52.843
♪♪♪

12:52.843 --> 12:55.405
JACK, IT MIGHT NOT BE
ANY OF MY BUSINESS, BUT...

12:55.405 --> 12:57.808
WHAT HAPPENED TO HER
WHEN SHE LIVED IN MY HOUSE?

12:57.808 --> 13:00.480
I REMEMBER WHEN I WAS, UH...

13:00.480 --> 13:01.982
WHEN I WAS A KID,

13:01.982 --> 13:03.483
MY OLD MAN TRIED
TO EXPLAIN TO ME THAT, UH,

13:03.483 --> 13:06.186
THAT HER DAD HAD BEEN ARRESTED,
AND I DIDN'T GET IT,

13:06.186 --> 13:08.558
'CAUSE MR. CLARKE WAS ALWAYS
SUCH A NICE GUY.

13:08.558 --> 13:10.420
BUT THEN WHEN I WAS OLD ENOUGH,

13:10.420 --> 13:12.292
I STARTED READING
EVERYTHING ABOUT IT,

13:12.292 --> 13:14.124
ABOUT HOW HE WAS RESPONSIBLE

13:14.124 --> 13:16.997
FOR BRINGING DOWN
A WHOLE PLANE FULL OF PEOPLE.

13:16.997 --> 13:19.930
AND AS FOR AMANDA...

13:19.930 --> 13:23.003
IT'S LIKE SHE JUST VANISHED.

13:23.003 --> 13:25.375
I THINK MY CHILDHOOD
PRETTY MUCH...

13:25.375 --> 13:27.838
ENDED AT THE SAME TIME.

13:27.838 --> 13:29.209
(indistinct conversations)

13:29.209 --> 13:31.811
(Amanda, crying) CAN'T I TAKE
SAMMY WITH ME?

13:31.811 --> 13:35.345
I'M SURE YOUR FRIEND
WILL TAKE GOOD CARE OF THE DOG.
 (Sammy whining)

13:35.345 --> 13:36.516
WON'T YOU, JACK?

13:36.516 --> 13:38.488
THE BEST. I SWEAR.

13:38.488 --> 13:40.120
SAY GOOD-BYE, AMANDA.

13:40.120 --> 13:42.492
(Sammy whines)

13:44.294 --> 13:45.325
(yelps)

13:45.325 --> 13:48.328
(Amanda continues crying)

13:49.960 --> 13:52.532
(continues crying)

13:52.532 --> 13:54.304
(Sammy whines)
 I'LL COME BACK FOR YOU.

13:54.304 --> 13:56.436
I PROMISE.

13:56.436 --> 13:58.909
I PROMISE.
I'LL COME BACK FOR YOU.

13:58.909 --> 14:00.540
I'LL COME BACK!

14:00.540 --> 14:02.172
IT WASN'T HER FAULT.

14:02.172 --> 14:04.844
UM...

14:04.844 --> 14:06.546
♪♪♪

14:06.546 --> 14:09.519
WOULD YOU MIND
GIVING THIS TO AMANDA?

14:09.519 --> 14:12.282
♪♪♪

14:12.282 --> 14:13.884
I'M SURE SHE HAS
SOME WARM MEMORIES

14:13.884 --> 14:15.025
OF LIVING THERE, TOO.

14:15.025 --> 14:16.456
MAYBE SPENDING SOME TIME
IN THE HOUSE

14:16.456 --> 14:17.888
WILL HELP HER REMEMBER THEM.

14:17.888 --> 14:20.931
YOU'RE A REALLY GOOD PERSON,
YOU KNOW THAT?

14:20.931 --> 14:24.564
♪♪♪

14:28.138 --> 14:29.599
(Sammy whines)

14:29.599 --> 14:31.001
(whimpers)

14:33.073 --> 14:34.945
(man) ♪ YOU'RE IN MY DREAMS ♪

14:34.945 --> 14:37.577
♪ YOU'RE IN MY DREAMS ♪

14:37.577 --> 14:40.550
♪ YOU'RE IN MY DREAMS,
YOU'RE IN MY DREAMS ♪

14:40.550 --> 14:43.383
YOU TAKE CARE OF HIM FOR ME,
OKAY?

14:43.383 --> 14:45.615
♪ YOU'RE IN MY DREAMS,
YOU'RE IN ♪

14:45.615 --> 14:47.357
STAY.
 (whines)

14:47.357 --> 14:52.362
♪ MY DREAMS ♪

14:59.629 --> 15:01.671
YOU'D THINK
WITH A 200K COMMISSION,

15:01.671 --> 15:03.603
YOU'D HAVE SETTLED SOMEWHERE
A LITTLE FLASHIER BY NOW.

15:03.603 --> 15:05.435
WHAT THE HELL, DANNY?
YOU SCARED THE CRAP OUT OF ME.

15:05.435 --> 15:07.237
YOU THINK IT'S TIME YOU FOUND
A PLACE OF YOUR OWN?

15:07.237 --> 15:08.908
ALREADY STARTED LOOKING.

15:08.908 --> 15:10.110
YEAH, WELL, LOOK FASTER.

15:10.110 --> 15:11.181
WELL, IT'S A MATTER OF TIME

15:11.181 --> 15:12.983
BEFORE I FILL THE VOID
IN THAT CORNER OFFICE

15:12.983 --> 15:14.344
RIGHT NEXT TO YOUR FATHER.

15:14.344 --> 15:17.347
I'M ASSUMING THAT'S WHERE ALL
THIS HOSTILITY IS COMING FROM.

15:17.347 --> 15:19.389
MY DAD'S BEEN TRYING FOR
TEN YEARS TO LAND NOLAN ROSS,

15:19.389 --> 15:21.421
AND YOU DO IT IN ONE NIGHT.

15:21.421 --> 15:22.953
WHAT'S YOUR SECRET?

15:22.953 --> 15:25.225
IF I TOLD YOU,
I'D HAVE TO KILL YOU.

15:25.225 --> 15:27.527
SINCE WHEN DID WE START
HIDING THINGS FROM EACH OTHER?

15:27.527 --> 15:28.999
NOTHING TO HIDE, DANNY.

15:28.999 --> 15:31.701
I JUST FIGURED OUT
WHAT MAKES NOLAN TICK.

15:31.701 --> 15:33.403
IT'S A GIFT.

15:33.403 --> 15:35.465
OH, SURE IT IS.

15:35.465 --> 15:37.167
MM.

15:40.940 --> 15:41.972
(door closes)

15:56.286 --> 15:57.657
(bottle clatters)

15:57.657 --> 15:59.489
(groans)

16:07.437 --> 16:10.100
(knock on door)

16:10.100 --> 16:12.042
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

16:17.077 --> 16:18.048
(sighs)

16:18.048 --> 16:20.050
HI.
 I'M GLAD YOU SHOWED.

16:20.050 --> 16:21.681
I THOUGHT MAYBE YOU'D GONE
COMPLETELY ROGUE ON ME.

16:21.681 --> 16:24.114
I-I DIDN'T MEAN TO TELL JACK
OUR SECRET.

16:24.114 --> 16:25.585
IT JUST HAPPENED.

16:25.585 --> 16:27.087
I JUST DON'T WANT HIM
TO GET HURT.

16:27.087 --> 16:29.059
THAT MAKES TWO OF US.

16:29.059 --> 16:31.591
JACK'S THE BEST THING
THAT'S EVER HAPPENED TO ME...

16:31.591 --> 16:33.263
BESIDES YOU.

16:33.263 --> 16:34.764
HE MENTIONED THAT YOU HAVE
A HARD TIME

16:34.764 --> 16:37.127
TALKING ABOUT
YOUR CHILDHOOD MEMORIES.

16:37.127 --> 16:39.529
(laughs) THAT'S ONLY BECAUSE
HE REMEMBERS MORE OF THIS STUFF

16:39.529 --> 16:41.571
THAN YOU ACTUALLY TOLD ME.

16:45.305 --> 16:47.437
WHAT'S THIS?

16:47.437 --> 16:49.709
IT'S A DIARY
FROM WHEN I WAS IN FOSTER CARE.

16:49.709 --> 16:51.041
IF YOU'RE GONNA BE
AMANDA CLARKE,

16:51.041 --> 16:53.083
YOU NEED TO KNOW
ABSOLUTELY EVERYTHING,

16:53.083 --> 16:55.715
ESPECIALLY THE TRUTH
ABOUT THE GRAYSONS.

16:55.715 --> 16:57.417
WHAT TRUTH?

16:57.417 --> 17:00.250
HEY, BABE.

17:00.250 --> 17:01.591
OH, I'M SORRY.

17:01.591 --> 17:03.022
I DIDN'T REALIZE
YOU HAD COMPANY.

17:03.022 --> 17:05.125
DANIEL,
THIS IS AMANDA CLARKE.

17:05.125 --> 17:08.098
AMANDA, DANIEL.

17:08.098 --> 17:10.359
NICE TO MEET YOU.

17:10.359 --> 17:13.403
LIKEWISE.

17:13.403 --> 17:15.135
I WAS JUST LEAVING.

17:15.135 --> 17:17.067
FEEL FREE
TO COME BY ANYTIME.

17:18.738 --> 17:20.410
(door opens)

17:20.410 --> 17:22.172
AMANDA CLARKE?
 (door closes)

17:22.172 --> 17:23.542
AS IN DAVID CLARKE'S
DAUGHTER?

17:23.542 --> 17:26.146
AS IN JACK'S NEW GIRLFRIEND.

17:26.146 --> 17:30.120
WAIT. YOU'RE NOT TALKING ABOUT
THAT DAVID CLARKE?

17:30.120 --> 17:32.552
WHAT, YOU DIDN'T KNOW?
HE USED TO OWN THIS PLACE.

17:32.552 --> 17:34.624
OH, MY GOD.

17:34.624 --> 17:39.829
MY REALTOR CONVENIENTLY
NEGLECTED TO MENTION THAT.

17:39.829 --> 17:41.231
YEAH, WELL, I DIDN'T
REALLY KNOW THEM,

17:41.231 --> 17:43.093
BUT HER FATHER WAS WORKING
FOR MY FATHER

17:43.093 --> 17:44.394
WHEN ALL THOSE PEOPLE
WERE KILLED.

17:44.394 --> 17:46.236
HOW HORRIBLE
FOR YOUR FAMILY.

17:46.236 --> 17:47.737
WELL, IT WAS
A LONG TIME AGO.

17:47.737 --> 17:49.469
I MEAN...

17:49.469 --> 17:51.441
YEAH.

17:51.441 --> 17:53.743
HOW WAS THE REST OF YOUR DAY?

17:53.743 --> 17:56.776
WELL, I DECIDED NOT TO TELL
MY FATHER ABOUT TYLER.

17:58.108 --> 17:59.779
HE'LL DIG HIS OWN GRAVE.

17:59.779 --> 18:02.112
THE ONLY WAY
FOR ME TO TRULY BEAT HIM

18:02.112 --> 18:03.213
SHOULD BE ON MERIT.

18:03.213 --> 18:04.384
I LIKE THAT PLAN.

18:04.384 --> 18:06.786
GREAT. THEN I HOPE YOU WON'T
MIND JOINING ME TONIGHT

18:06.786 --> 18:08.388
FOR DINNER WITH MR. TAKEDA.

18:08.388 --> 18:10.260
I'M GONNA NEED
MY JAPANESE TRANSLATOR.

18:10.260 --> 18:11.191
(laughs)

18:11.191 --> 18:12.362
OF COURSE.

18:12.362 --> 18:14.194
YOU'RE A GEM.

18:15.365 --> 18:17.167
I'M GONNA TAKE A SHOWER.

18:17.167 --> 18:18.698
OKAY.

18:20.770 --> 18:24.204
♪♪♪

18:24.204 --> 18:25.635
(indistinct conversations)

18:25.635 --> 18:27.477
(Amanda)
HEY, FANCY PANTS,

18:27.477 --> 18:29.209
COME HERE OFTEN?

18:29.209 --> 18:31.381
(man) ♪ I WAS RAISED
WITH BOTH... ♪

18:31.381 --> 18:33.343
BUY A GIRL A DRINK?

18:33.343 --> 18:35.185
YEAH, I DON'T GET IT.

18:35.185 --> 18:37.347
YOU COULD BE
NIBBLING CROISSANTS

18:37.347 --> 18:38.748
NEXT TO THE LOUVRE.

18:38.748 --> 18:41.251
INSTEAD YOU'RE SHELLING PEANUTS
IN SOME DIVE BAR

18:41.251 --> 18:45.124
WHERE, LET'S FACE IT,
NOBODY WANTS YOU.

18:45.124 --> 18:47.297
WELL, I THINK JACK
WOULD DISAGREE.

18:47.297 --> 18:48.798
EMILY, TOO.

18:48.798 --> 18:51.861
SHE'S REALLY EMBRACING THE IDEA
OF HAVING ME AROUND,

18:51.861 --> 18:55.535
EVEN AGREED THAT I'D CONTINUE
USING HER NAME.

18:55.535 --> 18:56.636
AW.

18:56.636 --> 18:58.768
SOMEBODY'S JEALOUS.

18:58.768 --> 19:01.241
(Declan) YEAH,
THERE ARE TWO ON THE LEASE.

19:01.241 --> 19:03.273
IT'S ME AND MY GIRLFRIEND.

19:03.273 --> 19:07.177
NO, I'LL BE 18 BY THE END
OF THE MONTH, SO IT'S...

19:07.177 --> 19:09.519
LET ME CALL YOU RIGHT BACK.

19:09.519 --> 19:11.321
(cell phone beeps
and clatters)

19:11.321 --> 19:12.282
WHAT WAS THAT ABOUT?

19:12.282 --> 19:13.483
UM...

19:13.483 --> 19:15.625
ME AND CHARLOTTE ARE GETTING
A PLACE TOGETHER.

19:15.625 --> 19:17.227
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA. WHAT?

19:17.227 --> 19:18.458
LOOK, THINK ABOUT IT,
OKAY?

19:18.458 --> 19:20.460
YOU AND ME ARE CROWDING
EACH OTHER UP HERE.

19:20.460 --> 19:22.232
AND--AND THINGS ARE MOVING
FORWARD WITH YOU AND AMANDA,

19:22.232 --> 19:23.863
SO IT'S--
WE NEED PRIVACY.

19:23.863 --> 19:25.235
DECLAN, LISTEN TO ME.

19:25.235 --> 19:26.196
THIS IS
A SPECTACULARLY BAD IDEA

19:26.196 --> 19:27.367
ON SO MANY LEVELS.

19:27.367 --> 19:28.738
YOU DON'T HAVE THE MONEY.

19:28.738 --> 19:30.300
YOU HAVEN'T FINISHED
HIGH SCHOOL.

19:30.300 --> 19:31.641
WHAT'S THE PLAN?

19:31.641 --> 19:32.802
GONNA BE A BAR BACK
THE REST OF YOUR LIFE?

19:32.802 --> 19:34.244
I'M DROWNING DOWNSTAIRS

19:34.244 --> 19:35.745
'CAUSE YOU CAN BARELY EVEN
DO THAT RIGHT.
 OKAY.

19:35.745 --> 19:38.208
HIRE SOMEONE ELSE.

19:38.208 --> 19:40.850
I'VE GOT MY OWN MONEY,
AND CHARLOTTE NEEDS ME.

19:40.850 --> 19:42.552
SHE NEEDS YOU?
 YEAH.

19:42.552 --> 19:45.255
DECLAN, YOU'RE JUST A KID.

19:45.255 --> 19:48.258
WHAT YOU NEED IS TO FINISH
HIGH SCHOOL, GO TO COLLEGE.

19:48.258 --> 19:50.460
YOU NEED TO MAKE YOURSELF
INTO THE KIND OF MAN

19:50.460 --> 19:52.492
THAT A GIRL LIKE
CHARLOTTE GRAYSON DESERVES.

19:52.492 --> 19:53.693
IF SHE'S STILL AROUND
AFTER THAT,

19:53.693 --> 19:54.864
THEN YOU GUYS CAN TALK ABOUT
HAVING A FUTURE.

19:54.864 --> 19:56.666
OTHERWISE, YOU'RE JUST...

19:56.666 --> 19:58.768
YOU'RE JUST THROWING
BOTH OF YOURS AWAY.

19:58.768 --> 20:01.771
♪♪♪

20:04.203 --> 20:06.676
YOUR CRUSADE FOR A FUTURE BUILT
ON SUSTAINED, RENEWABLE ENERGY

20:06.676 --> 20:08.378
IS ADMIRABLE

20:08.378 --> 20:10.280
AND A CAUSE
I PROUDLY STAND BEHIND.

20:10.280 --> 20:13.283
(speaking Japanese)

20:17.247 --> 20:20.219
(speaking Japanese)

20:20.219 --> 20:22.592
HE SAYS THAT HE...

20:22.592 --> 20:23.893
IS IMPRESSED BY YOUR RESEARCH

20:23.893 --> 20:25.895
AND RESPECTS
YOUR BUSINESS ETHICS.

20:25.895 --> 20:27.897
WELL, IT'S WHAT HE CAN EXPECT
ON A DAILY BASIS

20:27.897 --> 20:31.431
SHOULD HE CHOOSE TO TRUST ME
WITH HIS BUSINESS.

20:31.431 --> 20:34.434
(speaking Japanese)

20:40.239 --> 20:43.242
(speaking Japanese)

20:54.424 --> 20:55.525
(sighs)

20:55.525 --> 20:58.388
(speaks Japanese)

21:03.533 --> 21:05.765
(speaks Japanese)

21:11.441 --> 21:13.803
SO HE'S STILL ON THE FENCE?

21:16.976 --> 21:18.448
NO.

21:18.448 --> 21:20.880
WHAT DID HE SAY?

21:20.880 --> 21:24.454
HE'S AGREED
TO INVEST WITH YOU.

21:24.454 --> 21:26.356
$50 MILLION. (laughs)

21:26.356 --> 21:29.859
(laughing)

21:32.522 --> 21:34.524
WHEW.

21:39.769 --> 21:41.901
(Nolan) WHAT,

21:41.901 --> 21:45.875
NO SYNCHRONIZED SWIM
WITH YOUR SECRET SHARER?

21:45.875 --> 21:49.709
SINGLE WHITE FEMALE TOLD ME
YOU INVITED HER INTO THE FOLD.

21:49.709 --> 21:50.980
WHAT, I'M GUESSING

21:50.980 --> 21:53.413
THIS IS A KEEP YOUR FRENEMIES
CLOSE TYPE SITUATION?

21:53.413 --> 21:54.944
AT LEAST SHE'S
UNDER CONTROL, NOLAN.

21:54.944 --> 21:57.817
THAT'S MORE THAN I CAN SAY
FOR YOU AND TYLER.

21:59.849 --> 22:01.821
ABOUT THAT. UH...

22:01.821 --> 22:04.854
WELL, OPERATION TYLER HIT
A BIT OF A SPEED BUMP AND--

22:04.854 --> 22:06.556
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

22:06.556 --> 22:09.098
I'VE GOT THAT
UNDER CONTROL, TOO.

22:10.730 --> 22:12.331
BYE, NOLAN.

22:16.936 --> 22:18.968
(Conrad)
WHILE WE'RE BUYING THE UPSIDE,

22:18.968 --> 22:21.571
WE'RE SHORTING
THE POOREST PERFORMERS

22:21.571 --> 22:22.812
IN THAT SECTOR.

22:22.812 --> 22:24.444
SIMULTANEOUSLY COLLECTING
THE BEST IN BREED

22:24.444 --> 22:25.745
AND WEEDING OUT
THE RUNTS.

22:25.745 --> 22:27.747
YOU CATCH ON FAST, SON.

22:27.747 --> 22:29.118
(both laugh)

22:29.118 --> 22:30.480
TYLER, DAD.
 AH.

22:30.480 --> 22:32.021
THERE HE IS,
THE MAN OF THE HOUR.

22:32.021 --> 22:33.022
AH.

22:33.022 --> 22:34.524
DID I MISS SOMETHING?

22:34.524 --> 22:38.027
DANIEL MANAGED TO GET MR. TAKEDA
TO INVEST LAST NIGHT.

22:38.027 --> 22:39.489
$50 MILLION.

22:39.489 --> 22:41.090
(indistinct conversations)

22:41.090 --> 22:43.092
HOW'S THAT CORNER OFFICE
LOOKING FOR YOU NOW?

22:43.092 --> 22:45.765
$50 MILLION. WOW.

22:45.765 --> 22:47.537
SHAME YOU WON'T BE
GETTING COMMISSIONED.

22:47.537 --> 22:48.768
UM, YEAH.

22:48.768 --> 22:51.040
THAT COMMISSION WAS
A ONETIME INCENTIVE.

22:51.040 --> 22:52.702
TYLER DID BEAT YOU
TO THE PUNCH.

22:52.702 --> 22:54.704
BUT YOU KEEP TAKING
INITIATIVE LIKE THAT,

22:54.704 --> 22:57.807
AND I PROMISE,
COMMISSIONS WILL ABOUND.

22:57.807 --> 22:59.779
(Tyler) THAT'S RIGHT.

22:59.779 --> 23:02.712
SO LONG AS YOUR CLIENTS
ARE ALL JAPANESE.

23:02.712 --> 23:06.756
DON'T FORGET TO CUT IN
YOUR PRETTY BLONDE TRANSLATOR.

23:11.020 --> 23:13.693
THAT'S OKAY.
YOU CAN LET HIM GET TO YOU.

23:13.693 --> 23:16.696
ENVY CAN BE
A POWERFUL MOTIVATOR.

23:16.696 --> 23:17.827
MM.

23:17.827 --> 23:20.500
I DON'T ENVY TYLER, DAD.

23:20.500 --> 23:22.502
(indistinct conversations
continue)

23:22.502 --> 23:24.734
(front desk bell dings)

23:24.734 --> 23:25.905
IN FACT...

23:26.976 --> 23:28.808
THERE'S SOMETHING
YOU NEED TO KNOW

23:28.808 --> 23:31.781
ABOUT HOW HE GOT NOLAN ROSS
TO INVEST WITH YOUR COMPANY.

23:31.781 --> 23:32.842
(Amanda) GOOD BOY, SAMMY.

23:32.842 --> 23:35.144
GOOD BOY. YEAH.
 (barks)

23:35.144 --> 23:36.686
ATTABOY, SAMMY.
 (laughs)

23:36.686 --> 23:38.788
LOOKS LIKE SOMEONE'S MEMORY
IS COMING BACK.

23:38.788 --> 23:41.551
SAM'S NOT THE ONLY ONE.

23:41.551 --> 23:45.054
I FOUND THIS
ON THE BEACH THIS MORNING.

23:45.054 --> 23:46.626
IT REMINDED ME
OF HOW YOU AND I

23:46.626 --> 23:47.997
USED TO COLLECT
THAT SEA GLASS.

23:47.997 --> 23:49.799
YOU HAD A THING
FOR THE BLUE.

23:49.799 --> 23:53.132
WE BURIED JARS OF THAT STUFF
ALL OVER THE PLACE.

23:53.132 --> 23:55.905
SAID IT WAS
OUR SECRET TREASURE, REMEMBER?

23:55.905 --> 23:57.837
LIKE IT WAS YESTERDAY.

23:57.837 --> 24:02.011
(man) ♪ I WON'T
EVER BE ALONE AGAIN ♪

24:02.011 --> 24:04.173
(Ryan) I WAS VERY HAPPY
TO GET YOUR CALL, VICTORIA.

24:04.173 --> 24:06.516
I'M VERY AWARE OF THE JOB
YOU DID FOR MICHAEL

24:06.516 --> 24:08.548
IN HIS DIVORCE
AGAINST LYDIA.

24:08.548 --> 24:09.849
AND I THINK
IT WOULD BE FOOLISH OF ME

24:09.849 --> 24:11.951
NOT TO CONSIDER
YOUR COUNSEL.

24:11.951 --> 24:13.683
THANK YOU.

24:13.683 --> 24:16.556
IT SEEMS MY REPUTATION
PRECEDES ME.

24:16.556 --> 24:19.629
(chuckles) I SAW MICHAEL
EARLIER THIS SUMMER,

24:19.629 --> 24:22.562
ALREADY WITH A PRETTY
YOUNG WOMAN AT HIS ARM.

24:22.562 --> 24:23.993
I TRUST HE'S DOING WELL?

24:23.993 --> 24:25.595
ENGAGED.

24:25.595 --> 24:26.796
GOD HELP HIM.

24:26.796 --> 24:28.938
OBVIOUSLY,
HIS HEART IS FARING

24:28.938 --> 24:30.740
A LITTLE BIT BETTER
THAN LYDIA'S.

24:30.740 --> 24:33.202
COULDN'T HELP BUT FEEL BADLY
WHEN I HEARD THAT SHE HAD

24:33.202 --> 24:35.044
JUMPED FROM HER BALCONY.

24:35.044 --> 24:38.177
WELL,
YOU REAP WHAT YOU SOW.

24:38.177 --> 24:40.610
WELL, BEFORE WE DISCUSS
MY FEE,

24:40.610 --> 24:44.584
I'LL NEED YOU TO AGREE TO
SOME NONNEGOTIABLE CONDITIONS.

24:44.584 --> 24:45.885
I SEE.

24:45.885 --> 24:47.587
FIRST CONDITION--

24:47.587 --> 24:51.761
NO CONTACT WHATSOEVER
WITH YOUR SPOUSE, STARTING NOW.

24:51.761 --> 24:54.063
THAT WON'T BE A PROBLEM.
(laughs)

24:54.063 --> 24:55.795
SECOND--

24:55.795 --> 24:59.498
I NEED ABSOLUTE FINANCIAL
TRANSPARENCY FROM YOU--

24:59.498 --> 25:01.831
BANK ACCOUNTS, LOCK BOXES,

25:01.831 --> 25:04.133
PLANES, HOUSES, JEWELRY.

25:05.775 --> 25:07.837
THERE'S NO NEED
FOR THE DRAMATIC PAUSES,

25:07.837 --> 25:09.508
MR. HUNTLEY.

25:09.508 --> 25:12.742
IF I DISAGREE WITH YOUR TERMS,
I'LL LET YOU KNOW.

25:12.742 --> 25:13.783
FINALLY,

25:13.783 --> 25:15.745
AND MOST IMPORTANTLY,

25:15.745 --> 25:18.147
I NEED YOU TO BE WILLING
TO DO WHATEVER IT TAKES

25:18.147 --> 25:19.749
TO WIN YOUR CASE,

25:19.749 --> 25:22.521
WHICH COULD MEAN YOU END UP
WITH A SIGNIFICANT AMOUNT

25:22.521 --> 25:24.994
OF CONRAD'S BLOOD ON YOUR HANDS
BY THE TIME THIS IS OVER.

25:24.994 --> 25:27.927
I WOULDN'T HAVE IT
ANY OTHER WAY.

25:31.701 --> 25:32.832
(bead curtain clatters)

25:32.832 --> 25:34.764
HEY. WE'RE GONNA BE LATE
FOR OUR APARTMENT MEETINGS.

25:36.035 --> 25:37.306
WE'RE NOT
GONNA BE LATE, CHARLOTTE,

25:37.306 --> 25:38.968
BECAUSE I CANCELED 'EM.

25:38.968 --> 25:40.840
YOU DON'T WANT
TO MOVE IN WITH ME?

25:40.840 --> 25:45.645
I-I'VE NEVER WANTED
ANYTHING MORE.

25:45.645 --> 25:48.147
BUT IT CAN'T BE
LIKE THIS.

25:48.147 --> 25:50.620
YOU--YOU HAVE A NICE LIFE
CARVED OUT FOR YOU HERE.

25:50.620 --> 25:51.881
YEAH, AND YOU'RE A PART
OF IT NOW.

25:51.881 --> 25:53.883
YEAH. I WANT TO BE
A PART OF IT FOREVER.

25:53.883 --> 25:57.086
BUT IF WE'RE GONNA LAST,
THEN I HAVE TO FINISH SCHOOL.

25:57.086 --> 26:00.830
I DON'T KNOW,
MAYBE GO TO COLLEGE.

26:00.830 --> 26:03.963
YOU DESERVE A GUY
LIKE THAT.

26:03.963 --> 26:05.234
WELL,

26:05.234 --> 26:07.236
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
DO THIS JUST FOR ME.

26:07.236 --> 26:08.938
WELL, I'M NOT.

26:08.938 --> 26:10.900
I'M DOING IT FOR US.

26:10.900 --> 26:12.702
HERE'S YOUR MOM'S CHECK.

26:12.702 --> 26:15.244
KEEP IT.

26:15.244 --> 26:18.908
THINK OF IT AS MY MOTHER'S
INVESTMENT IN YOUR FUTURE.

26:18.908 --> 26:20.349
IT'S NOT MY STYLE.

26:20.349 --> 26:22.011
I'LL FIND ANOTHER WAY.

26:27.286 --> 26:29.919
YOU WANTED TO SEE ME, SIR?

26:29.919 --> 26:31.360
YEAH.

26:31.360 --> 26:32.862
IT'S COME TO MY ATTENTION

26:32.862 --> 26:34.924
YOU GARNERED MR. ROSS' SUPPORT

26:34.924 --> 26:38.798
THROUGH LESS-THAN-HONORABLE
CIRCUMSTANCES.

26:38.798 --> 26:42.231
SO YOUR TIME HERE
AT GRAYSON GLOBAL IS OVER.

26:42.231 --> 26:45.034
WITH ALL DUE RESPECT,
WHO CARES HOW I GOT HIM?

26:45.034 --> 26:46.906
$20 MILLION
FROM A GUY THAT

26:46.906 --> 26:49.078
YOU'VE BEEN TRYING TO LAND
FOR A DECADE IS HARDLY--

26:49.078 --> 26:51.841
THIS COMPANY'S WORTH
OVER 200 TIMES THAT,

26:51.841 --> 26:54.914
WHICH IS WHY WE TRY TO AVOID
SCANDAL AT ALL COST.

26:54.914 --> 26:58.017
BLACKMAILING A POTENTIAL CLIENT
INTO A PORTFOLIO

26:58.017 --> 27:00.920
FALLS DIRECTLY
INTO THE SCANDALOUS CATEGORY.

27:00.920 --> 27:02.121
BLACKMAIL?

27:02.121 --> 27:04.153
THE SEX TAPE YOU MADE
WITH NOLAN ROSS?

27:04.153 --> 27:05.995
(chuckles) SEX TAPE?
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

27:05.995 --> 27:07.697
SAVE YOUR BREATH.

27:07.697 --> 27:08.928
YOU'RE FIRED.

27:13.062 --> 27:14.403
AM I?

27:16.405 --> 27:20.069
AT LEAST WHEN I DO BUSINESS,
PEOPLE DON'T DIE.

27:20.069 --> 27:22.211
I BEG YOUR PARDON?

27:22.211 --> 27:24.844
YOU WANT A SCANDAL?

27:24.844 --> 27:27.316
YOU FIRE ME,
AND I TELL THE WORLD

27:27.316 --> 27:29.218
THAT YOU AND YOUR WIFE
WERE THE REAL REASON

27:29.218 --> 27:31.650
ALL THOSE PEOPLE DIED
ON FLIGHT 197

27:31.650 --> 27:32.882
AND THAT
THAT GUY WHO WORKED FOR YOU,

27:32.882 --> 27:33.983
DAVID CLARKE,

27:33.983 --> 27:36.155
WAS JUST A PATSY.

27:37.687 --> 27:39.859
I'D THINK VERY CAREFULLY
ABOUT THE NEXT WORDS

27:39.859 --> 27:43.863
THAT COME OUT OF YOUR MOUTH,
MR. GRAYSON.

27:48.768 --> 27:51.100
(rustling)

27:51.100 --> 27:53.202
(exhales)

27:53.202 --> 27:55.404
EXCUSE ME.

27:55.404 --> 27:57.076
CAN I HELP YOU?

27:57.076 --> 27:59.348
I'M, UH,
LOOKING FOR SOMETHING

27:59.348 --> 28:00.850
I BURIED AS A LITTLE KID.

28:00.850 --> 28:03.312
YEAH, WELL, I DON'T THINK
IT'S COOL FOR YOU TO BE HERE

28:03.312 --> 28:04.854
WITHOUT EMILY AROUND.

28:04.854 --> 28:07.286
WELL, EMILY SAID IT'S COOL,
SO...

28:07.286 --> 28:08.417
SHE DIDN'T MENTION IT TO ME,

28:08.417 --> 28:09.959
SO YOU SHOULD PROBABLY
COME BACK WHEN SHE'S HERE.

28:09.959 --> 28:11.721
DO YOU HAVE A PROBLEM
WITH ME?

28:11.721 --> 28:13.062
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW ME.

28:13.062 --> 28:15.364
EXACTLY.

28:15.364 --> 28:17.396
WHAT'S GOING ON?

28:17.396 --> 28:19.368
YOUR BOYFRIEND HERE IS TRYING
TO THROW ME OFF YOUR PROPERTY

28:19.368 --> 28:22.271
FOR LOOKING FOR SOMETHING
THAT BELONGS TO ME.

28:22.271 --> 28:23.773
NO, IT'S OKAY, DANIEL.

28:23.773 --> 28:26.335
UM, WELL, MAYBE YOU COULD, UH,
COME BACK TOMORROW MORNING,

28:26.335 --> 28:28.237
AND I'LL HELP YOU SEARCH
FOR WHAT YOU'RE TRYING TO FIND.

28:29.779 --> 28:31.240
TOLD YOU SHE WAS COOL.

28:34.413 --> 28:37.186
THAT GIRL MAKES ME NERVOUS.

28:37.186 --> 28:40.850
SHE JUST SEEMS
A LITTLE... LOST TO ME.

28:40.850 --> 28:42.191
I MEAN, CAN YOU IMAGINE

28:42.191 --> 28:43.893
GROWING UP
THE WAY SHE HAD TO?

28:43.893 --> 28:46.856
JUST BE CAREFUL WITH HER.

28:46.856 --> 28:49.398
I WILL.

28:53.833 --> 28:55.404
(computer beeps)

28:55.404 --> 28:57.436
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

28:57.436 --> 28:58.808
CAN YOU TELL ME
WHY YOU'RE LOOKING FOR

28:58.808 --> 29:00.870
A 1-BEDROOM APARTMENT
IN MONTAUK?

29:00.870 --> 29:02.912
YOU'RE SPYING ON MY LAPTOP?

29:02.912 --> 29:04.443
DON'T CHANGE THE SUBJECT.

29:05.815 --> 29:08.317
DECLAN AND I
WERE LOOKING FOR A PLACE.

29:08.317 --> 29:11.250
THOUGHT WE'D PUT
YOUR $25,000 BRIBE

29:11.250 --> 29:13.052
TO GOOD USE.

29:13.052 --> 29:14.753
THAT'S RIGHT, MOM.

29:14.753 --> 29:15.754
I KNOW YOU WERE TRYING
TO PAY HIM OFF,

29:15.754 --> 29:16.926
ONLY YOU COULDN'T,

29:16.926 --> 29:18.487
BECAUSE HE REALLY CARES
ABOUT ME.

29:18.487 --> 29:20.759
I'M SURE HE DOES.

29:20.759 --> 29:22.391
AND I'M SURE THAT YOU THINK
YOU FEEL THE SAME WAY, TOO,

29:22.391 --> 29:24.934
BUT BELIEVE ME, THIS IS
AN INSANELY BAD IDEA.

29:24.934 --> 29:27.096
WHAT ABOUT SCHOOL?
WHAT ABOUT--

29:27.096 --> 29:29.168
RELAX, MOM. I'M NOT...
MOVING IN WITH DECLAN.

29:29.168 --> 29:30.870
IT WOULDN'T BE FAIR
TO HIM.

29:30.870 --> 29:32.171
FAIR TO HIM?

29:32.171 --> 29:35.044
BECAUSE ALL I REALLY WANT
IS TO GET AWAY FROM YOU.

29:36.545 --> 29:38.007
I'M 17, MOM,

29:38.007 --> 29:39.809
AND DAD SAID IT'S PRETTY MUCH
UP TO ME

29:39.809 --> 29:42.411
WHO I WANT TO LIVE WITH.

29:42.411 --> 29:44.153
(voice breaking)
WELL, GUESS WHAT.

29:44.153 --> 29:46.355
I CHOOSE DAD.

29:48.487 --> 29:50.019
(Tyler)
HOW ARE THE PLANS

29:50.019 --> 29:53.422
FOROURMONTE CARLO GETAWAY
COMING ALONG?

29:54.824 --> 29:56.465
ON HOLD, I'M AFRAID.

29:56.465 --> 29:58.797
(sighs)

29:58.797 --> 29:59.999
REALLY?

29:59.999 --> 30:01.800
AND WHY IS THAT?

30:01.800 --> 30:03.402
WELL,
BECAUSE THERE'S NO LONGER

30:03.402 --> 30:05.434
ANY REASON TO CELEBRATE.

30:05.434 --> 30:08.077
I'M SORRY, TY.

30:08.077 --> 30:09.578
I'M PULLING MY INVESTMENT.

30:09.578 --> 30:12.111
UH, I'M HAVING
TOO MANY SECOND THOUGHTS.

30:12.111 --> 30:13.812
(chuckles)

30:15.945 --> 30:18.547
YOU'VE BEEN PLAYING ME
THIS WHOLE TIME.

30:18.547 --> 30:22.451
SETTING ME UP TO FAIL.

30:22.451 --> 30:24.994
(chuckles) LET'S NOT MIX
BUSINESS AND PLEASURE.

30:24.994 --> 30:26.455
OH, FUNNY COMING FROM THE GUY

30:26.455 --> 30:29.228
WHO VIDEOTAPED
THAT SICKENING ENCOUNTER.

30:29.228 --> 30:31.060
EXCUSE ME?

30:31.060 --> 30:34.263
I HAVE TO SAY, I'M SHOCKED
THAT YOU WOULD EXPOSE YOURSELF

30:34.263 --> 30:36.535
TO CONRAD GRAYSON
JUST TO RUIN ME.

30:36.535 --> 30:39.308
I UNDERESTIMATED YOU,
BUT THEN...

30:39.308 --> 30:42.541
YOU UNDERESTIMATED ME, TOO.

30:42.541 --> 30:46.845
I ONLY MADE THAT TAPE
AS INSURANCE

30:46.845 --> 30:50.249
BECAUSE I DIDN'T TRUST YOU.

30:50.249 --> 30:52.851
SO, TYLER, HOW MUCH IS IT GONNA
COST FOR ME TO GET IT BACK?

30:52.851 --> 30:55.184
(chuckles)

30:55.184 --> 30:57.256
WELL, NOLAN,

30:57.256 --> 30:59.058
YOUDO NOT
 WANT TO PLAY GAMES WITH ME.

30:59.058 --> 31:01.430
YOU KNOW I DON'T HAVE IT,
SO WHERE IS IT?! SHOW ME!

31:01.430 --> 31:03.562
(whispers)
SHH, SHH, TY, TY, STOP.

31:03.562 --> 31:05.194
(inhales deeply)

31:05.194 --> 31:06.865
(exhales)

31:12.241 --> 31:13.402
(clicks)

31:13.402 --> 31:15.544
(clicks keyboard keys)

31:15.544 --> 31:18.047
(whoosh)

31:18.047 --> 31:20.879
(Tyler) I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU REALLY DID THIS.

31:20.879 --> 31:24.213
I DIDN'T GIVE THIS
TO CONRAD GRAYSON. I SWEAR.

31:24.213 --> 31:27.286
YEAH, RIGHT. THEN WHO DID?

31:27.286 --> 31:29.518
YOU STUPID...

31:29.518 --> 31:30.889
SON OF A BITCH.

31:30.889 --> 31:32.521
WAIT, WAIT. WAIT.

31:32.521 --> 31:34.093
TY!

31:44.633 --> 31:48.377
WE COULD'VE BEEN
A GOOD TEAM.

31:48.377 --> 31:49.538
NOW YOU'RE JUST AS LONELY
AND PATHETIC

31:49.538 --> 31:51.941
AS THE DAY I FOUND YOU.

31:56.145 --> 31:57.446
♪♪♪

31:57.446 --> 31:58.948
(door opens)

31:58.948 --> 32:01.951
♪♪♪

32:11.460 --> 32:13.562
SURPRISE.

32:13.562 --> 32:14.964
(gasps)

32:14.964 --> 32:17.006
YOU DID NOT
DO ALL THIS FOR ME.

32:17.006 --> 32:18.607
WHO ELSE?

32:18.607 --> 32:20.669
(sighs)

32:20.669 --> 32:23.242
(laughs)
SOMETHING WRONG?

32:23.242 --> 32:24.573
I WANTED
TO SURPRISE YOU, TOO,

32:24.573 --> 32:27.346
SO... I LOOKED FOR
THE SEA GLASS WE BURIED,

32:27.346 --> 32:30.479
BUT... I COULDN'T FIND IT
ANYWHERE.

32:30.479 --> 32:33.482
I GUESS MY MEMORY SUCKS
AFTER ALL.

32:33.482 --> 32:35.084
YOUR MEMORY IS PERFECT.

32:35.084 --> 32:38.157
♪♪♪

32:38.157 --> 32:40.429
(rattles)

32:40.429 --> 32:41.690
WHERE'D YOU FIND THAT?

32:41.690 --> 32:44.033
RIGHT WHERE YOU LEFT IT.

32:44.033 --> 32:46.395
I DUG IT UP THE DAY AFTER
SOCIAL SERVICES TOOK YOU AWAY

32:46.395 --> 32:48.737
AND I'VE KEPT IT EVER SINCE.

32:48.737 --> 32:50.369
♪♪♪

32:50.369 --> 32:53.342
THAT IS SO... INCREDIBLE.

32:53.342 --> 32:55.244
♪♪♪

32:55.244 --> 32:57.246
AND NOW YOU'VE COME BACK
FOR IT,

32:57.246 --> 32:59.148
JUST LIKE YOU SAID YOU WOULD.

32:59.148 --> 33:01.510
AMONG OTHER THINGS.

33:01.510 --> 33:02.511
SAMMY?

33:02.511 --> 33:03.682
(laughs)

33:03.682 --> 33:05.254
YOU.

33:05.254 --> 33:06.515
(chuckles)

33:06.515 --> 33:09.118
♪♪♪

33:10.559 --> 33:12.261
(Emily)
SOMETHING'S UPSETTING YOU.

33:12.261 --> 33:15.724
I HOPE IT'S NOT
MY SWORDFISH. (chuckles)

33:15.724 --> 33:17.666
NO, NO,
THE DINNER WAS PERFECT.

33:17.666 --> 33:18.667
BUT I...

33:18.667 --> 33:20.329
I THINK I SHOULD GO HOME.

33:20.329 --> 33:22.271
WHY?

33:22.271 --> 33:24.203
THERE'S SOMETHING ABOUT THE WAY
TYLER WAS ACTING TODAY.

33:24.203 --> 33:25.604
I JUST WANT TO MAKE SURE
HE LEAVES TOWN

33:25.604 --> 33:27.206
WITHOUT TORCHING THE PLACE.

33:27.206 --> 33:28.637
BUT THANK YOU FOR DINNER.

33:28.637 --> 33:30.339
YOU'RE WELCOME.

33:30.339 --> 33:32.041
I'M SORRY YOU HAVE TO DEAL
WITH ALL OF THIS.

33:32.041 --> 33:33.542
OH, IT'S ALL RIGHT,

33:33.542 --> 33:35.714
AS LONG AS I STILL GOT YOU
AT THE END OF THE DAY.

33:50.659 --> 33:53.162
YOU'RE IN LOVE WITH HIM.

33:54.703 --> 33:57.706
OF COURSE I'M NOT.

33:57.706 --> 34:00.669
WHEN YOU CAME TO ME,

34:00.669 --> 34:03.342
YOU WERE
JUST A LITTLE GIRL...

34:03.342 --> 34:06.044
SO MUCH RAGE,

34:06.044 --> 34:08.647
SO MUCH BETRAYAL.

34:08.647 --> 34:11.780
I DID NOT WANT TO TRAIN YOU
BECAUSE...

34:11.780 --> 34:15.053
YOUR EMOTIONS...

34:15.053 --> 34:17.456
DESTINED YOU TO FAIL.

34:17.456 --> 34:19.788
I'M NOT THAT GIRL ANYMORE.

34:19.788 --> 34:22.091
I'VE SEPARATED MYSELF
FROM MY EMOTIONS.

34:22.091 --> 34:24.132
THEN YOU ARE LYING.

34:24.132 --> 34:25.833
I WOULD NEVER LIE TO YOU.

34:25.833 --> 34:27.436
THEN YOU LIE

34:27.436 --> 34:31.239
EVEN TO YOURSELF.

34:32.841 --> 34:35.704
I CAN DO NOTHING MORE
TO HELP YOU.

34:38.177 --> 34:39.348
PLEASE.

34:41.250 --> 34:43.181
DON'T ABANDON ME.

34:43.181 --> 34:46.185
THE DECISION WAS YOURS.

34:48.587 --> 34:50.518
YOU ARE

34:50.518 --> 34:52.791
ON YOUR OWN.

35:03.732 --> 35:04.773
(groans)

35:04.773 --> 35:07.676
(smacks keyboard keys)

35:07.676 --> 35:08.807
(whooshes)

35:08.807 --> 35:09.778
(clicks)

35:09.778 --> 35:10.809
(whoosh)

35:10.809 --> 35:12.110
(clicks key, computer chirps)

35:12.110 --> 35:13.742
HOW DOES THIS SOUND?

35:13.742 --> 35:15.884
THE GRAYSONS ARE INCREDIBLY
POWERFUL, YOUR HONOR.

35:15.884 --> 35:18.787
I WAS INTIMIDATED INTO HELPING
THEM FRAME DAVID CLARKE

35:18.787 --> 35:20.889
AND THEN THREATENED BY
THEIR HEAD OF SECURITY

35:20.889 --> 35:22.821
IF I DIDN'T COMPLY.

35:22.821 --> 35:26.455
THE PROSECUTION RESTS.

35:33.462 --> 35:35.464
(door opens and closes)

35:40.409 --> 35:42.911
MOM?

35:42.911 --> 35:44.543
YOU OKAY?

35:44.543 --> 35:46.875
CHARLOTTE'S GONE.

35:46.875 --> 35:50.419
SHE WENT TO GO LIVE
WITH YOUR FATHER. (laughs)

35:50.419 --> 35:51.580
(inhales)

35:51.580 --> 35:54.353
I'M SORRY. I...

35:54.353 --> 35:55.654
LISTEN, YOU KNOW HER.

35:55.654 --> 35:57.656
SHE'LL COOL OFF
AND COME HOME EVENTUALLY.

35:57.656 --> 35:59.428
WELL, THIS MAUSOLEUM

35:59.428 --> 36:02.431
IS TOO COLD AND EMPTY
TO BE CALLED A HOME.

36:04.433 --> 36:06.495
I'M AFRAID I'VE GIVEN
EVERYONE IN THIS FAMILY

36:06.495 --> 36:08.737
A REASON TO DESERT ME.

36:08.737 --> 36:11.200
WELL, I'M STILL HERE
FOR YOU.

36:12.841 --> 36:14.843
THANK YOU
FOR CHECKING UP ON ME.

36:14.843 --> 36:16.545
OF COURSE.

36:16.545 --> 36:19.308
I ALSO WANTED TO MAKE SURE
TYLER HAD LEFT WITHOUT A FUSS.

36:19.308 --> 36:20.479
WELL, YOU JUST MISSED HIM.

36:20.479 --> 36:21.810
HE WENT TO DINNER
A FEW MINUTES AGO.

36:21.810 --> 36:23.612
WAIT.
TYLER'S STILL STAYING HERE?

36:23.612 --> 36:24.953
YES, AS FAR AS I KNOW.

36:30.919 --> 36:33.492
(cell phone rings)

36:33.492 --> 36:34.963
DANIEL.

36:34.963 --> 36:38.567
DAD, WHAT HAPPENED TO TYLER
WHEN YOU FIRED HIM?

36:38.567 --> 36:41.300
ACTUALLY...
I DIDN'T HAVE TO FIRE HIM.

36:41.300 --> 36:42.901
We, uh, settled the matter.

36:42.901 --> 36:44.803
WHAT THE HELL
DOES THAT MEAN?

36:44.803 --> 36:47.236
It means I don't have to
explain myself to you, Daniel.

36:47.236 --> 36:48.777
THIS IS ABOUT BUSINESS.

36:48.777 --> 36:49.978
BUSINESS?

36:49.978 --> 36:51.780
WHAT ABOUT ETHICS
AND INTEGRITY?

36:51.780 --> 36:53.211
WELL, HE PROMISED

36:53.211 --> 36:55.384
TO RESOLVE THE SITUATION
WITH NOLAN DISCREETLY.

36:55.384 --> 36:56.585
AND YOU BELIEVED HIM?

36:56.585 --> 36:58.617
THIS IS NOT YOUR CALL,
DANIEL.

36:58.617 --> 37:00.919
(beeps)

37:00.919 --> 37:03.652
DANIEL?

37:03.652 --> 37:04.623
(knock on door)

37:04.623 --> 37:06.255
(beeps)

37:10.429 --> 37:11.860
CHARLOTTE.

37:11.860 --> 37:14.703
DADDY, I CAN'T LIVE
WITH HER ANYMORE.

37:14.703 --> 37:17.936
OH, SWEETHEART.
COME HERE.

37:19.638 --> 37:22.571
(whispers) IT'S OKAY.

37:22.571 --> 37:24.012
(Funkservice International)
 ♪ LIFE IS GOOD ♪

37:24.012 --> 37:28.417
